# Summer Sprout Budget - UI & Styling Guidelines

## Color Palette
- **Primary Color**: Vibrant green (`#A0D6B4`) - symbolizes growth and new beginnings
- **Background Color**: Light green (`#E5F0E7`) - very desaturated for soft, pleasing UI
- **Accent Color**: Yellow (`#D4AC0D`) - contrasts beautifully with green shades for highlights
- **Text Colors**: Use appropriate contrast ratios with the green backgrounds

## Typography
- **Font Family**: 'PT Sans' - humanist sans-serif for readability and modern look
- Apply to both body text and headlines consistently

## Icon Guidelines
- **Income/Spending Icons**: Use line icons (not filled)
- **Tips/Suggestions**: Feature lightbulb icons
- Maintain consistent icon style throughout the application

## Layout & Responsiveness
- **Card-like Style**: Apply to all screens (mobile, tablet, desktop)
- **Calendar Interface**: Must be fully responsive across all screen sizes
- **Gentle Transitions**: Use smooth transition effects for:
  - Month navigation in calendar
  - Data entry interactions
  - Component state changes

## Component Standards
All UI components should follow shadcn/ui patterns with Summer Sprout customizations:
- Use Tailwind CSS classes with the established color palette
- Ensure accessibility standards are met
- Implement consistent spacing and typography scales
- Apply card-style layouts where appropriate

